{{Infobox company | name = CodinGame | logo = CodinGame_logo.svg | logo_size = 350px | type = Online coding platform<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2015/11/11/with-codingame-learning-to-code-becomes-a-game |title=With CodinGame, Learning To Code Becomes A Game |author=Romain Dillet |date={{date|2015-11-11}} |website=[[TechCrunch]] |access-date={{date|2016-10-18}} }}</ref> | industry = | founded = 2012 | founder = | hq_location_city = | hq_location_country = | area_served = Worldwide | key_people = CodinGame / Jean Lafleur ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]]), Frédéric Desmoulins ([[Chief operating officer|COO]]), Nicolas Antoniazzi ([[Chief technology officer|CTO]]), Aude Barral ([[Chief marketing officer|CMO]]) | products = | owner = | num_employees = 20<ref>{{fr}} {{cite web | author =Sylvie Brouillet | title =Comment le Montpelliérain CodinGame a réussi à monter un hackathon avec... Warner Bros |url=http://www.usine-digitale.fr/article/comment-le-montpellierain-codingame-a-reussi-a-monter-un-hackathon-avec-warner-bros.N449412 |date={{date|2016-10-10}} | website =[[L'Usine nouvelle|L’Usine Digitale]]}}</ref> | website = {{URL|codingame.com}} }}
'''CodinGame''' is a technology company editing an online platform for developers, allowing them to play with programming with increasingly difficult puzzles, to learn to code better with an online programming application supporting twenty-five programming languages, and to compete in multiplayer programming contests involving timed artificial intelligence, or code golf challenges.
CodinGame also serves as a recruiting platform, allowing developers to get noticed by companies based on their performance on the contests.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.i-programmer.info/news/204-challenges/6626-codingame-contest-for-fun-and-employment.html |title=CodinGame Contest For Fun and Employment |author=Sue Gee |date={{date|2013-11-21}} |website=I-programmer.info |access-date={{date|2016-10-18}} }}</ref>
== History ==
{{Expand section|date=October 2016}}
== Activity ==
CodinGame's business model is based on sponsoring by companies wanting to get in touch with developers. CodinGame helps these company to recruit developers through worldwide contests hosted every three months,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.i-programmer.info/news/204-challenges/9677-smash-the-code-make-an-impression-with-codingame.html |title=Smash The Code Make An Impression With CodinGame |author=Sue Gee |date={{date|2016-04-26}} |website=I-programmer.info |access-date={{date|2016-10-18}} }}</ref> or private hackathons. The startup was also seeded through several fundraisings in 2013 and 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.isai.fr/en/news/1427-codingame-raises-16-million-to-become-the-must-have-gaming-platform-for-programmers.html |title=CodinGame Raises $1.6 Million to Become the Must-have Gaming Platform for Programmers |date={{date|2015-11-11}} |website={{Interlanguage link multi|ISAI|fr}} |access-date={{date|2016-10-18}} }}</ref>
CodinGame for Work sells also turnkey tech screening solution to help companies assess the level of their programmer candidates through coding tests.
Available programming languages for solving puzzles or taking part in contests are: [[C (programming language)|C]], [[C++]], [[C Sharp (programming language)|C#]], [[Bourne-Again shell|Bash]], [[Clojure]], [[Dart (programming language)|Dart]], [[F Sharp (programming language)|F#]], [[Go (programming language)|Go]], [[Groovy (programming language)|Groovy]], [[Java (programming language)|Java]], [[JavaScript]], [[Haskell (programming language)|Haskell]], [[Kotlin (programming language)|Kotlin]], [[Lua (programming language)|Lua]], [[Objective-C]], [[OCaml]], [[Pascal (programming language)|Pascal]], [[Perl]], [[PHP]], [[Python (programming language)|Python]] (v2 and v3), [[Ruby (programming language)|Ruby]], [[Rust (programming language)|Rust]], [[Scala (programming language)|Scala]], [[Swift (programming language)|Swift]] and [[Visual Basic .NET]].
